author: Special to syracuse.com
title: Super DIRT Week 2015: Danny Johnson wins at Weedsport
text:
By Dick O'Brien
Danny Johnson passed Brett Hearn on the 58th lap, and pulled away to an impressive $4,000 triumph in Wednesday night's 75-lap Super DIRTcar Series race for 358 Modifieds at Weedsport Speedway.
Johnson pressured leader Brett Hearn for nearly 50 laps before making his winning pass with 17 laps remaining.
Hearn wound up second, with Pat Ward, Billy Decker, Erick Rudolph, Matt Sheppard, Larry Wight, Ryan Susice, Jimmy Phelps and Gary Lindberg completing the top-10 finishers.
A strong field of 50 358-modifieds was on hand at Al Heinke's newly renovated Weedsport Speedway.
